Tallitsch has performed as a jazz saxophonist for over 25 years (bandleader/composer and sideman) throughout the United States, Europe, and South America.
His most recent recording is All Together Now (Posi-Tone, 2015)
His fifth album for Posi-Tone, "All Together Now" was recorded in New York City in 2014 and released in April 2015.
Tallitsch is currently Musical Director, and Composer for the multi-media dance company, The Big Sky Project, founded by Carrie Ellmore-Tallitsch.
Tallitsch currently tutors jazz saxophone students in Princeton, New Jersey and teaches piano students with autism at The Princeton Child Development Institute.
